createNewTradingPropertyGroup

private TradingPropertyGroup createNewTradingPropertyGroup(TradingPropertyClassType classTypeWrapper,
                                                           java.lang.String sessionName,
                                                           java.lang.Integer classKeyInteger)
                                                    throws java.lang.reflect.InvocationTargetException
Creates a new TradingPropertyGroup representing the passed attributes. If the new TradingPropertyGroup is one of the known three Simple** types, then it will be further initialized so that it knows which TradingPropertyType that it represents.

Parameters:
classTypeWrapper - to find the representative implementation of TradingPropertyGroup for, for instantiation.
sessionName - for new TradingPropertyGroup to represent
classKeyInteger - for new TradingPropertyGroup to represent
Returns:
newly instantiated implementation of a TradingPropertyGroup, who's real class implements the type as represented in the passed classTypeWrapper
Throws:
java.lang.reflect.InvocationTargetException - will be thrown if the implementation could not be instantiated.
